sequenceDiagram
    participant User as User Browser
    participant Router as OpenShift Router<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant Gateway as Gateway (Envoy)<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant AuthProxy as kube-auth-proxy<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS TLS (svc CA)
    participant OAuth as OpenShift OAuth Server<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant App as Application Service<br/>varies HTTP/HTTPS

    Note over User, App: Flow 1: User Authentication via Gateway (OAuth Mode)

    User->>Router: GET /app<br/>HTTPS/443, TLS 1.2+, No Auth
    Router->>Gateway: Forward to Gateway
    Gateway->>AuthProxy: ext_authz check<br/>HTTPS/8443, TLS (svc CA)<br/>Cookie: _oauth2_proxy
    AuthProxy-->>Gateway: 401 Redirect (no session)
    Gateway-->>User: 302 Redirect to OAuth
    User->>OAuth: Login form<br/>HTTPS/443, TLS 1.2+<br/>User credentials
    OAuth-->>User: 302 Redirect with auth code
    User->>Gateway: GET /oauth2/callback<br/>HTTPS/443, TLS 1.2+<br/>Authorization code
    Gateway->>AuthProxy: ext_authz callback<br/>HTTPS/8443
    AuthProxy->>OAuth: Exchange code for token<br/>HTTPS/443, OAuthClient credentials
    OAuth-->>AuthProxy: Access token + ID token
    AuthProxy-->>Gateway: 200 OK, Set-Cookie: _oauth2_proxy
    Gateway-->>User: 302 Redirect to /app (with cookie)
    User->>Router: GET /app (with cookie)
    Router->>Gateway: Forward
    Gateway->>AuthProxy: ext_authz check (cookie valid)
    AuthProxy-->>Gateway: 200 OK (x-forwarded-access-token)
    Note over Gateway: Lua filter extracts token,<br/>strips _oauth2_proxy cookies
    Gateway->>App: Forward request<br/>Authorization: Bearer {token}
    App-->>Gateway: Response
    Gateway-->>User: Response

    Note over User, App: Flow 2: Component Deployment via DSC

    participant Admin as Cluster Admin
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API<br/>6443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant DSCCtrl as DSC Controller<br/>(operator pod)
    participant CompCtrl as Component Controller<br/>(operator pod)

    Admin->>K8sAPI: Create DataScienceCluster CR<br/>HTTPS/6443, Bearer Token
    K8sAPI-->>DSCCtrl: Watch event (DSC created)
    DSCCtrl->>K8sAPI: Create Component CRs<br/>HTTPS/6443, SA Token
    K8sAPI-->>CompCtrl: Watch event (Component CR)
    CompCtrl->>K8sAPI: Server-side apply manifests<br/>HTTPS/6443, SA Token
    CompCtrl->>K8sAPI: Check deployment status<br/>HTTPS/6443, SA Token
    K8sAPI-->>DSCCtrl: Component status update
    DSCCtrl->>K8sAPI: Aggregate DSC status<br/>HTTPS/6443, SA Token

    Note over User, App: Flow 3: Monitoring Stack Data Collection

    participant Prom as MonitoringStack<br/>Prometheus<br/>9090/TCP HTTP
    participant OTELCol as OTEL Collector<br/>varies gRPC/HTTP
    participant Tempo as Tempo<br/>4317/TCP gRPC
    participant Thanos as ThanosQuerier<br/>9090/TCP HTTP
    participant Perses as Perses<br/>varies HTTP

    Prom->>App: Scrape metrics<br/>varies HTTP/HTTPS<br/>SA Token
    OTELCol->>App: Collect traces<br/>varies gRPC/HTTP<br/>SA Token
    OTELCol->>Tempo: Export traces<br/>gRPC/4317, TLS (optional)
    Thanos->>Prom: Query metrics<br/>HTTP/9090, SA Token
    Perses->>Prom: Query metrics<br/>varies HTTP, SA Token
    Perses->>Tempo: Query traces<br/>varies HTTP, SA Token
